 Joys of men v. women: Who does what?
 A man and his wife were having an argument about who should brew the coffee
each morning.
=20
 The wife said, 'You should do it because you get up first, and then we don=
't
have to wait as long to get our coffee.
=20
 The husband said, 'You are in charge of cooking around here and you should=
 do
it, because that is your job, and I can just wait for my coffee.'
=20
 Wife replies, 'No, you should do it, and besides, it is in the Bible that =
the
man should do the coffee.'
=20
 Husband replies, ' I can't believe that, show me.'
=20
 So she fetched the Bible, and opened the New Testament and showed him at t=
he
top of several pages, that it indeed says 'HEBREWS'
