            <b>Leading INRA facility reports robust genetic analysis result=
s from=20
            Fluidigm BioMark=99 System<br>
            </b><br>
            Number One Agricultural Institute in Europe Brings World-leadin=
g Integrated=20
            Fluidic Circuit Technology to All European Researchers<br>
            <br>
            South San Francisco, Calif., July 20, 2010 =96 Fluidigm Corpora=
tion=20
            today announced that the Toulouse Midi-Pyr=E9n=E9es Genomic Pla=
tform -=20
            Genotoul INRA core facility is now providing a wide range of se=
rvices=20
            on a BioMark=99 System for Genetic Analysis to a wide range of =
French=20
            researchers. These services include SNP genotyping, gene expres=
sion=20
            analysis and digital PCR quantification of DNA libraries for ne=
xt-generation=20
            sequencing. The INRA has been validating the performance of the=
 system=20
            on several projects over the past year.<br>
            <br>
            =93We have used the BioMark system for many different applicati=
ons and=20
            have found the results to be very robust and comparable to thos=
e obtained=20
            using classical techniques. However, this platform allows us to=
 provide=20
            researchers with a lot more high-quality data, in a fraction of=
 the=20
            time, at a very affordable cost. In addition, we were the first=
 facility=20
            to offer Fluidigm technology in France and are delighted that w=
e are=20
            seeing the demand for this technology increasing nicely,=94 sai=
d Denis=20
            Milan, group leader of the Department of Animal Genetics at INR=
A.<br>
            <br>
            The INRA Genomic Platform core facility offers researchers acce=
ss=20
            to the world=92s most-advanced life science tools through the o=
rganization=92s=20
            service center, which is also open to scientists from other ins=
titutes.=20
            Many species, such as human, pig, mouse, rat, chicken, Macaque,=
 and=20
            many more, have been studied at this facility.<br>
            <br>
            Fluidigm's BioMark system has already been used in large-scale =
projects=20
            such as the European Commission Program Diogenes (Diet, Obesity=
 and=20
            Genes; www.diogenes-eu.org).<br>
            &quot;We recently analyzed the expression of 288 genes in 1500 =
adipose=20
            tissue samples from obese subjects undergoing dietary intervent=
ions.=20
            We are confident that this approach will be a major step forwar=
d in=20
            the characterization of biomarkers of obesity complications&quo=
t;=20
            said Dominique Langin, Head of the National Institute of Health=
 and=20
            Medical Research (Inserm) and Paul Sabatier University Obesity =
Research=20
            Laboratory.<br>
            <br>
             =93We are delighted and honored that INRA is using our BioMark=
 System=20
            and Fluidigm chips to bring gene expression, genotyping and dig=
ital=20
            PCR capabilities to European researchers. Having an organizatio=
n with=20
            the worldwide reputation of the Genotoul INRA core facility (Na=
tional=20
            Institute of Agricultural Research) capitalizing on the versati=
lity=20
            and capabilities of our integrated fluidic circuit (IFC) techno=
logy=20
            affords Fluidigm a great opportunity to demonstrate how much va=
lue=20
            we can bring to a wide range of research,=94 said Gajus Worthin=
gton,=20
            president and chief executive officer, Fluidigm.<br>
            <br>
            Fluidigm=92s BioMark system is a highly versatile, high-through=
put,=20
            high-performance genetic analysis platform. It enables a variet=
y of=20
            applications, including disease tissue profiling, single cell g=
ene=20
            expression, ultra-high throughput genotyping, and absolute quan=
titation=20
            via digital PCR. The system is equipped with features that sign=
ificantly=20
            enhance throughput, reduce costs by using microscopic amounts o=
f expensive=20
            reagents, and lessen hands-on time by having the chip automate =
the=20
            liquid-handling steps. Fluidigm=92s 96.96 Dynamic Array=99 IFCs=
 can provide=20
            researchers with 9,216 real-time data point reads, or 24 times =
the=20
            number of reads provided by a transitional single 384-well plat=
e,=20
            in the same amount of time.<br>
            <br>
            &gt;&gt;&gt; About INRA<br>
            INRA carries out mission-oriented research for high-quality and=
 healthy=20
            foods, competitive and sustainable agriculture and nutrition, t=
he=20
            environment and land use facing the world of agriculture and ag=
