            <b>Joys of men v. women: Who does what?<br>
            </b>A man and his wife were having an argument about who should=
 brew=20
            the coffee each morning.<br>
            <br>
            The wife said, 'You should do it because you get up first, and =
then=20
            we don't have to wait as long to get our coffee.<br>
            <br>
            The husband said, 'You are in charge of cooking around here and=
 you=20
            should do it, because that is your job, and I can just wait for=
 my=20
            coffee.'<br>
            <br>
            Wife replies, 'No, you should do it, and besides, it is in the =
Bible=20
            that the man should do the coffee.'<br>
            <br>
            Husband replies, ' I can't believe that, show me.'<br>
            <br>
            So she fetched the Bible, and opened the New Testament and show=
ed=20
            him at the top of several pages, that it indeed says 'HEBREWS'<=
